text: New Jersey's 5th congressional district is a United States congressional district in New Jersey, which elects a representative to the United States House of Representatives. Bergen County, Passaic County, Sussex County, and Warren County are counties that are part of the congressional district. Democrat Josh Gottheimer became the representative in 2016. ==Election history== Election results from presidential races Year Office Results 2000 President Bush 52 - 45% 2004 President Bush 57 - 43% 2008 President McCain 54 - 45% 2012 President Romney 50.9 - 48.5% 2016 President Trump 48.8 - 47.7% ==References== Category:New Jersey Category:Congressional districts of New Jersey
